dilates() - Method in class org.bytedeco.mkldnn.mkldnn_convolution_desc_t
Convolution dilates in each spatial dimension.
dims() - Method in class org.bytedeco.mkldnn.mkldnn_memory_desc_t
Dimensions in the following order: - CNN data tensors: mini-batch, channel, spatial ({N, C, [[D,] H,] W}) - CNN weight tensors: group (optional), output channel, input channel, spatial ({[G,] O, I, [[D,] H,] W}) - RNN data tensors: time, mini-batch, channels ({T, N, C}) or layers, directions, states, mini-batch, channels ({L, D, S, N, C}) - RNN weight tensor: layers, directions, input channel, gates, output channels ({L, D, I, G, O}).
direction() - Method in class org.bytedeco.mkldnn.mkldnn_rnn_desc_t

SGEMM performs a matrix-matrix multiplication operation defined as C := alpha*op( A )*op( B ) + beta*C where - op( X ) is one of op( X ) = X or op( X ) = X**T, - alpha and beta are scalars, - A, B and C are matrices, with op( A ) an m by k matrix, op( B ) a k by n matrix and C an m by n matrix.
